# Core Standards

- Use strict TypeScript. Avoid `any`.
- Match existing naming, imports, and folder conventions.
- Keep changes minimal — one concern per change.
- Do not commit secrets (`.env`, API keys, tokens).
- Do not add dependencies without explicit approval.
- Remove unused imports, dead code, and debug logs before finishing.
